This document is an "IBM Batch Report" for Batch Number 7 from the Bangor Vote Collection Point (ID 2178) in NSW, associated with Electoral Event ID 19694. It was created on June 10, 2016, and reported on June 15, 2016. The report details the processing status of 50 individual ballots (numbered 1-50, with some non-sequential jumps, e.g., 9 to 14, 33 to 38). For each ballot, it provides results for various quality assurance and formality checks, including `QualityAssurance Checked`, `Initials Checked`, `Official Mark Checked`, `UnusualMarkings Checked`, `Formality Result Checked`, `Verification Action`, `Formality Reason Checked`, `ATL Preferences Checked`, `ATL Mismatches`, `ATL Saved Checked`, `ATL Breakdown Checked`, `ATL Formal Checked`, `BTL Preferences Checked`, `BTL Mismatches`, `BTL Saved Checked`, `BTL Breakdown Checked`, and `BTL Formal Checked`. All entries across all checks for all listed ballots in this specific batch are uniformly marked "OK".

This document is directly relevant to Vanessa Teague's FOI request [LEX540] for 'IBM Outputs', specifically as one of the 106 "IBM Batch Report" PDF files from 2016. It exemplifies the detailed reports providing ballot processing insights, batch metadata (Vote Collection Point, Batch Number, dates), electoral event context (NSW, 2016), and granular ballot-level checks (formality, initials, marks, preferences). While the FOI request overview indicates that checks like `UnusualMarkings Checked`, `Verification Action`, `Formality Reason Checked`, `ATL Mismatches`, and `BTL Mismatches` frequently show "HAS ISSUES" entries with alphanumeric codes in other reports, this particular document is notable for having "OK" results for all checks across all ballots, signifying a batch processed without any recorded anomalies or exceptions that required flagging.
